  "prompt": "Which \"is\" the best pair of in-ear earphones under Rs. 1000?",
  "response": "Finding the best pair of in-ear earphones under Rs. 1000 depends on your specific needs, such as sound quality, build, comfort, and features. Here are some highly recommended options as of 2023:\n\n### 1. **Boat Bassheads 152**\n   - **Pros**: Affordable, good bass, durable build, tangle-free cable.\n   - **Cons**: Average mids and highs.\n   - **Best For**: Bass lovers on a budget.\n\n### 2. **Realme Buds 2**\n   - **Pros**: Balanced sound, lightweight, and comfortable.\n   - **Cons**: Plastic build may not feel premium.\n   - **Best For**: Day-to-day use for casual listening.\n\n### 3. **JBL Endurance Run**\n   - **Pros**: Sweatproof, secure fit, good sound clarity.\n   - **Cons**: Slightly higher price (around Rs. 999).\n   - **Best For**: Fitness enthusiasts.\n\n### 4. **Sony MDR-EX155AP**\n   - **Pros**: Clear sound, comfortable, and durable.\n   - **Cons**: Bass may feel underwhelming for some.\n   - **Best For**: Those who prioritize clarity over bass.\n\n### 5. **pTron Tangent Lite**\n   - **Pros**: Affordable, sound quality, sturdy build.\n   - **Cons**: Bass could be better.\n   - **Best For**: Budget-conscious buyers.\n\n### 6. **Boat Rockerz 255 Pro+**\n   - **Pros**: Wireless, IPX7 water resistance, long battery life.\n   - **Cons**: Sound quality may not match wired options.\n   - **Best For**: Those seeking wireless convenience.\n\n### Final Recommendation:\nIf you prefer **wired earphones**, the **Boat Bassheads 152** or **Sony MDR-EX155AP** are excellent choices. For **wireless earbuds**, the **Boat Rockerz 255 Pro+** is a great option under Rs. 1000.\n\nAlways check for discounts or deals on platforms like Amazon, Flipkart, or the brand's official website to get the best value for your money.",
